      "message": "[Critical] Line 1878: 🔴 Critical: `fallbackClone({}, convId)` is invoked for every corrupted conversation without excluding conversations that have no persisted members or where the current device is the only member. In those cases the recovery path may repeatedly schedule clone attempts that can never succeed, replacing the previous endless fetch/merge retry loop with an endless re-clone retry loop. Gate recovery on recoverable metadata and at least one remote member device, or mark the conversation as unrecoverable until metadata changes.\n```suggestion\nfor (const auto\u0026 convId : toReclone) {\n    const auto it \u003d shared-\u003econvInfos_.find(convId);\n    if (it \u003d\u003d shared-\u003econvInfos_.end() || !shared-\u003ehasRemoteCloneSource(convId))\n        continue;\n    shared-\u003efallbackClone({}, convId);\n}\n```",
      "revId": "6e7918ea68245250ae3c2797068d91f2515ff672",
