      "message": "Line 3931: 🟡 Suggestion: `validate()` walks every commit and every tree/blob reachable from `HEAD` synchronously during startup for every conversation. Large conversations can make `loadConversations()` significantly slower, especially because this repeats work on every daemon start. Consider using libgit2\u0027s object database/graph verification primitives if available, or limiting the expensive full-history validation to cases where prior repository operations failed and using a cheaper `HEAD`/tree check on normal startup.",
